data.description: Don't miss out on this stunning house situated on a spacious 1.76-acre lot! With four bedrooms, two full bathrooms, this home offers ample space for comfortable living. Boasting over 2,324 square feet, it provides plenty of room for all your needs. Located in the charming Leigh Brook subdivision, the community has a low HOA fee of only $100 per year. As you approach the house, you'll be greeted by a delightful front porch, setting the stage for a warm welcome. Step inside to discover a cozy living/sitting room on the right and a formal dining room on the left. The family room is filled with natural light, thanks to four large windows, and features a gas fireplace for those cozy evenings. The kitchen is a chef's dream, with abundant cabinet space, a pantry, stainless steel appliances, and elegant granite countertops. Adjacent to the kitchen is a peaceful desk area that can be used as a small home office or computer room, connecting to the spacious laundry room. The master bedroom is generously sized and offers an en-suite bathroom, complete with a separate shower and a walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms also feature walk-in closets. There's even a versatile bonus room that can serve as a bedroom, hobby room, or game room. Finally, the property boasts a huge and serene lot, providing a tranquil atmosphere you won't want to miss. Located near the new Inland Pass project on Harbins Rd at Hwy 316, that will include a Publix & other retail, apartments, senior living units, community park & active recreation areas. Some other nearby projects are a gas station, fast food restaurant & the Rowan Project.
